On 18 March 2020 President Cortizo announced a national curfew between 9pm and 5am, effective immediately with limited exemptions. You should not leave your accommodation during these times unless it is an emergency.
Donâ€™t become involved with drugs in any way. Possession of even very small quantities can lead to imprisonment of up to 15 years. The judicial process is slow and prison conditions are very harsh.
Simply being in the company of someone who is using drugs is sufficient grounds for arrest. From the time of arrest, it can take two years before you even appear before a judge.
The Police and security forces are empowered to enforce restrictions on movements and events due to the current state of emergency in place to deal with the novel coronavirus outbreak. You should follow their instructions.
